HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 304
BY REPRESENTATIVE DESHOTEL
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Commends the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association on
the occasion of its seventy-fifth anniversary and designates May 20, 2026, as
Louisiana Oil Marketers Association Day in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association on the occasion of its seventy-fifth
3 anniversary and to designate Wednesday, May 20, 2026, as Louisiana Oil Marketers
4 Association Day in Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association (LOMA) represents more than
6 two hundred fifty member companies that own, operate, or supply over three thousand
7 convenience stores, service stations, car washes, truck stops, and related motor fuel retail
8 outlets throughout Louisiana; and
9 WHEREAS, LOMA members annually supply nearly three billion gallons of motor
10 fuel to serve Louisiana motorists and a wide range of commercial users, including farmers,
11 construction firms, and state and local governmental entities; and
12 WHEREAS, petroleum marketers play an essential role in the energy and
13 transportation infrastructure of Louisiana by ensuring the reliable distribution and resale of
14 refined petroleum products across wholesale and retail markets; and
15 WHEREAS, LOMA was founded seventy-five years ago by a group of jobbers
16 meeting at the Jung Hotel in Shreveport, Louisiana, who sought to establish an organization
17 to support and advance the petroleum marketing industry through shared services, advocacy,
18 and professional collaboration; and
19 WHEREAS, over the decades, LOMA has evolved into a statewide trade association
20 headquartered in Baton Rouge that provides political representation, educational
