1 programming, industry publications, scholarships, and annual conventions and trade shows
2 that strengthen Louisiana's convenience store and petroleum marketing industries; and
3 WHEREAS, LOMA continues to address the evolving needs of its members,
4 including fair competition, regulatory compliance, underground storage tank issues, fuel
5 theft prevention, and other matters critical to the industry; and
6 WHEREAS, LOMA members contribute significantly to the economy of Louisiana
7 by investing in local communities, creating jobs, and providing essential goods and services
8 in both urban and rural areas of the state; and
9 WHEREAS, the seventy-fifth anniversary of LOMA represents a milestone of
10 enduring service and economic contribution, and the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association
11 is deserving of recognition for its legacy of service to the citizens of the state.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
13 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the Louisiana Oil Marketers Association on
14 the occasion of its seventy-fifth anniversary and does hereby designate Wednesday, May 20,
15 2026, as Louisiana Oil Marketers Association Day in Louisiana.
